This paper discusses social information processing in the context of news aggregation, which involves information retrieval (IR) and social interaction (SI). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also touches on issues related to social dynamics (SD), cybersecurity (CY), and human-computer interaction (HC), which make these sub-categories also likely.
